<!-- Style Guide Notes -->
<div class="style-notes">
  <h2>Illustration Style Guide</h2>
  <div class="notes-grid">
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Visual Language</h4>
      <p>Modern biopharma illustration: organic cellular forms, molecular structures, and flowing connection lines. Soft radial gradients, not sharp geometry. Everything feels alive and in motion — representing biological processes and hope.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Color Palette</h4>
      <p>Always use the HPVCA purple/lavender spectrum. Layer opacities (5%–35%) for depth. White accents on dark backgrounds; purple accents on light backgrounds.</p>
      <div class="swatch">
        <span style="background:#3A1057;"></span>
        <span style="background:#5E2585;"></span>
        <span style="background:#7B3BA8;"></span>
        <span style="background:#A06AC4;"></span>
        <span style="background:#C9A4E2;"></span>
        <span style="background:#E8D5F5;"></span>
        <span style="background:#F5EEFB;"></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Do / Don't</h4>
      <p><strong>Do:</strong> Use soft ellipses, dashed paths, radial glows, low-opacity layers. Suggest science without literal diagrams.<br><br><strong>Don't:</strong> Use sharp corners, neon colors, cartoon-style icons, stock clipart, or overly clinical/cold imagery.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Where to Use</h4>
      <p><strong>Cellular Landscape:</strong> Hero backgrounds, page headers<br><strong>HPV Structure:</strong> "What is HPV?" content<br><strong>Shield:</strong> Vaccination/prevention pages<br><strong>Magnifier:</strong> Screening sections<br><strong>DNA Helix:</strong> Research, webinars<br><strong>Network:</strong> About, community, advocacy</p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Implementation</h4>
      <p>All illustrations are inline SVG — zero file weight, infinitely scalable, and editable in any code editor. Colors reference CSS variables for easy brand updates. Can be exported as SVG files for use in presentations, print, or Canva.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-card">
      <h4>Photography Pairing</h4>
      <p>Illustrations complement (don't replace) photography. Layer them behind founder portraits, use as card backgrounds alongside community photos, or as standalone graphics for science content where photography isn't available.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

